The neat thing about Progenitor is that it says "If this creature isn't a token."
If Progenitor comes in and copies a token that it has created, then Progenitor itself is not a token.
Therefore, the new Progenitor now creates two copies of that token on your upkeep.

Aight think tank, I need help making new [[Neheb, Dreadhorde Champion]] good. People are requesting Neheb vs Neheb for my next article.

New Neheb rummages cards. Obvious synergies include Psychosis Crawler and Alham's Archive, but they run thin thereafter. A way to use all those discarded cards is basically a necessity.

Thought 1: Daretti/Feldon. Fill graveyard with artifacts, use spells to bring them back.
 - Problem is that Neheb is probably less effective at this than just using Daretti

Thought 2: Load up the yard for one big Mizzix's Mastery. Use spells to replay dead spells in one big flourish.
 - Problem here is simply that there aren't many payoffs. Mizzix's Mastery is kind of eggs-in-one-basket.

Thought 3: I'm missing something
 - Problem with this is that it would be to admit that I'm a failure

Halp
